> **Theory Box: Why Embeddings Work**
>
> Embeddings map text into a high-dimensional space where *meaning* determines position. "Dog" and "puppy" land near each other; "dog" and "quantum" land far apart. ChromaDB uses a lightweight embedding model internally — in production, you'd use OpenAI, Cohere, or sentence-transformers for higher quality.

